snippet.title: A SKETCH basic javascript graph user plug-in
snippet.description: The vector graph application Sketch for Mac lets you develop your own plug-ins which makes it easy to automate tasks inside the vector graph application. This should make the path for many plug-ins, as many brilliant javascript developer exists around the globe. You can find the example simple plug-in here: https://gist.github.com/netsi1964/523a837385f0488498678a6fb5ea3ba2

snippet.title: ANUG: Holographic Programming – Exploring the HoloLens
snippet.description:
Virtual reality and augmented reality are terms most developers and technical enthusiasts recognize. What about “Mixed reality”? A reality that is part real world, part digital world, a reality that is enhanced with Holograms.

snippet.title: Visual Style Inspector in Webkit/Safari (Nightly)
snippet.description: The latest version of Webkit (Safari) has a cool visual inspector for editing the styles of a webpage. This video shows an example of editing a pen from CodePen: http://codepen.io/netsi1964/pen/KpjNOY
